<br>
From the basic player crafted armor you can find cheaply in bazaar, to tov armor easily farmed by less than a group, to elemental player made armor which is rare but still doable, you can get setup in basic level of gear very fast.  Most of the guilds that do xserver transfers have the money and provide it to get people setup.<br>
<br>
I dunno about these people but the bigger guilds that do it, it's nothing to gear someone up.  Not an overnight thing where suddenly they're as well equipped as the people that have been around, but they're equipped well enough to do the job.<br>
<br>
It's not that different from how it is if someone applies from the same server, I mean someone in tov armor applying to some big guild, may as well be naked comparitively.  That's why the big thing for the guilds is AA points, and flags. <br>
<br>
We've had a handful of people transfer over from other servers, and we had no problem helping them out and generally speaking, a good player is still good in weak gear, so they can get up to speed fast.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lyndarracuthalion>Lyndarra Cuthalion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#330000>(3/30/03 5:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=709.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/madlyknitting/catwoman.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &lt;In Virtue&gt; on Kane Bayle -recruitment-</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Coray:<br>
